5:
Multiple threats spotted! Captain,
what are your orders?
9:
We can handle this many enemies
no problem! Let's go!
24:
Quit messing around and snap out
of it already...
43:
Captain Alk, I believe my mistake
today requires further action!
51:
I would like you to discipline me.
Please hit me as hard as you can.
59: I failed to protect you back there!
63:
And the events that followed held
back our squadron as a whole...
67:
I intend to take responsibility! So
please, discipline me in any way you
see fit!
72:
What? No, I'm not gonna do that! 
It wasn't even really a mistake! 
We were just a little out of sync, 
that's all!
73:
And what kind of captain would
punish someone like that?
77: So... you will not discipline me?
82: Of course not! I would never!
86:
B-but I was unable to be your
shield...
94:
That ain't your duty, and Alk doesn't
need protecting... Calm down.
108: Why do you call Alk Captain?
116:
He just... reminds me of the captain
of my naval unit...
121: Really? What kind of person was he?
133:
Ah, d-don't misunderstand! 
Oh, how do I put this?
136:
The captain... He took in orphans like
me and raised us to be soldiers.
139:
He taught us that we were tools to
be used...
144: That doesn't sound like Alk at all.
149:
I-I suppose you're right. 
Now that I think about it, 
they're completely different...
152:
But my captain... would also make
meals for us often.
155:
I suppose that's what reminded me
of him...
160:
I am just a tool to be used for my
superior's plans. That is why I need
orders. I promise I will not fail next
time!
175:
That's right... Starview isn't a military
camp, and the people here aren't
soldiers or tools or whatever else.
179:
That's why I'm not going to give you
any orders. I want you to decide for
yourself what you want to do.
188:
Yes, sir. If you insist, then from now
on, I will make my own decisions.
193:
Surely you realize that this too is
following orders...
203:
Why don't we start with something
small? Like...
210:
B-but, um... you've already bought
the ingredients for tonight's dinner...
214:
We can just use these
tomorrow—feel free to pick
whatever you want.
218:
Fluffy, I like both seafood and meat
dishes.
222:
And I am in the mood for something
spicy.
228:
Wh-what? 
Th-then what should I pick?
232:
Calm down. There are no wrong
answers here.
235:
How about we take a look at the
shops in the area first? That might
give you some inspiration.
